# Product vision & core values gate

Full reference: `product-vision.md`. Read it before designing or building any
new feature, and cite which core value the work serves.

**Vision (short form):** Skulls and Trading is a **private club** for
disciplined investors and traders — a crew, not an audience. The app is the
club's flagship; the community is the treasure. Beta proves value to members
first; monetization is an MVP decision made on member evidence, never a launch
gate.

**Core values:** Discipline over dopamine · Integrity of the deck · Crew before
audience · The long voyage · Earn the treasure · Always learning · Craft over
content.

## When building features

- Answer the **feature gate checklist** at the bottom of `product-vision.md`
  (which value does this serve; does it keep the club a club; plan not gamble;
  long voyage; authored craft; monetize only after proof).
- If a requested feature conflicts with the vision or values (e.g. activity
  rewards, hype mechanics, audience-style leaderboards, AI-generated member
  art, unproven monetization), **stop and raise it** before building.
- Keep this rule and `product-vision.md` in sync with the Vision Board canvas
  if the user updates vision or values.
